I encountered this issue in eclipse 3.1.2.
The tried to install fresh 3.1 and still had the same issue.

The root cause is here:

java.lang.UnsupportedClassVersionError:
com/gehc/ce/mdmt/client/MdmtclientPlugin (Unsupported major.minor version 49.0)

You are running on:
java.version=1.4.2_03

So my guess is that you compiled your code for Java 1.5 (5.0) and are trying run it on 1.4 which wont work. 

Try setting your project (or workspace) to compile your code with the target set to 1.4. Then rebuild your bundles(plugins) and retry.

Also, if you are using java 5 language constructs and intend to only have your bundle runnable on 5.0 you should add to your manifest Bundle-RequiredExecutionEnvironment: J2SE-1.5
